Everyone knows that by default JAXB uses the no-argument constructor when instantiating objects. 
Readers of this blog are also familiar with using XmlAdapters to build objects.  
In this post I'll cover how the use of factory classes and methods can be configured 
through the @XmlType annotation.


We will use a factory class to create instances of Customer.  
The factory class must have a public, static, zero-argument method that 
returns an instance of the desired domain object.

